Title: Towards OM An Object-Oriented Implementation of Mantra  
Author: Greg Butler, Tania Kharma Ono Tjandra 
Address: Montreal Quebec H3G 1M8 Canada  Windsor Ontario Canada  
Affiliation: Department of Computer Science Concordia University  School of Computer Science University of Windsor  
Abstract: Mantra is a shell for hybrid knowledge representation and hybrid inferences. It supports three different formalisms: logic, frames, and semantic networks. Mantra was developed in Common Lisp at Karl-sruhe by Bittencourt and Calmet. The OM project seeks to re-engineer Mantra through the use of design patterns, the OMT notation, and C++ as the implementation language. The logic module forms the heart of Mantra. It uses Patel-Schneider's four-valued logic and a decidable inference algorithm, called t-entailment. Here we report on the design and implementation of the logic module, and the corresponding algorithms for unification and t-entailment. 
